Documentation

    The Java-based source code is documented using standard Javadocs.

    The C++-based JNI source code is documented using Natural Docs.

    All other languages are documented inline using language-specific comments.

File Names and Extensions

    JNI header files generated by javah have an extension of '.h'.

    C++ class definitions have an extension of '.hpp' and are named according to
    the class being defined.

    C++ class implementations have an extension of '.cpp' and are named according
    to the class implemented.

    Non-class-based C++ source code contains the '.cpp' extension with a
    filename describing the contents.

